decks.title: Hapatra, Vizier of Poisons
decks.description: Whenever Hapatra, Vizier of Poisons deals combat damage to a player, you may put a -1/-1 counter on target creature. Whenever you put one or more -1/-1 counters on a creature, create a 1/1 green Snake creature token with deathtouch.

card.name: Hapatra, Vizier of Poisons
card.oracle_text:
Whenever Hapatra, Vizier of Poisons deals combat damage to a player, you may put a -1/-1 counter on target creature.
Whenever you put one or more -1/-1 counters on a creature, create a 1/1 green Snake creature token with deathtouch.
card.flavor_text: Her subtle smile is suffused with venom.

card.name: Carnifex Demon
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Carnifex Demon enters the battlefield with two -1/-1 counters on it.
{B}, Remove a -1/-1 counter from Carnifex Demon: Put a -1/-1 counter on each other creature.
card.flavor_text: Every contagion has a host.

card.name: Channeler Initiate
card.oracle_text:
When Channeler Initiate enters the battlefield, put three -1/-1 counters on target creature you control.
{T}, Remove a -1/-1 counter from Channeler Initiate: Add one mana of any color.

card.name: Decimator Beetle
card.oracle_text:
When Decimator Beetle enters the battlefield, put a -1/-1 counter on target creature you control.
Whenever Decimator Beetle attacks, remove a -1/-1 counter from target creature you control and put a -1/-1 counter on up to one target creature defending player controls.

card.name: Demon of Catastrophes
card.oracle_text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice a creature.
Flying, trample
card.flavor_text: A pit yawned open, a column of oily smoke arose, and a towering form hissed, "I accept this offering."

card.name: Dusk Urchins
card.oracle_text:
Whenever Dusk Urchins attacks or blocks, put a -1/-1 counter on it.
When Dusk Urchins dies, draw a card for each -1/-1 counter on it.
card.flavor_text: They spawn from shadow, wreaking chaos until shadow claims them again.

card.name: Evolution Sage
card.oracle_text: Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, proliferate. (Choose any number of permanents and/or players, then give each another counter of each kind already there.)
card.flavor_text: "To care for yourself, cultivate the world. To care for the world, cultivate yourself."

card.name: Festering Mummy
card.oracle_text: When Festering Mummy dies, you may put a -1/-1 counter on target creature.
card.flavor_text: As its parched flesh withers away, its malignant hunger grows.

card.name: Fume Spitter
card.oracle_text: Sacrifice Fume Spitter: Put a -1/-1 counter on target creature.
card.flavor_text: "Our archers made sport of it as it fumbled its way up the slag ridge. As it collapsed we thought ourselves safe, but the foul thing carried more than necrogen." —Adaran, Tangle hunter

card.name: Generous Patron
card.oracle_text:
When Generous Patron enters the battlefield, support 2. (Put a +1/+1 counter on each of up to two other target creatures.)
Whenever you put one or more counters on a creature you don't control, draw a card.

card.name: Gravedigger
card.oracle_text: When Gravedigger enters the battlefield, you may return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
card.flavor_text: A full coffin is like a full coffer—both are attractive to thieves.

card.name: Ichorclaw Myr
card.oracle_text:
Infect (This creature deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters and to players in the form of poison counters.)
Whenever Ichorclaw Myr becomes blocked, it gets +2/+2 until end of turn.

card.name: Necroskitter
card.oracle_text:
Wither (This deals damage to creatures in the form of -1/-1 counters.)
Whenever a creature an opponent controls with a -1/-1 counter on it dies, you may return that card to the battlefield under your control.

card.name: Obelisk Spider
card.oracle_text:
Reach
Whenever Obelisk Spider deals combat damage to a creature, put a -1/-1 counter on that creature.
Whenever you put one or more -1/-1 counters on a creature, each opponent loses 1 life and you gain 1 life.

card.name: Pitiless Plunderer
card.oracle_text: Whenever another creature you control dies, create a Treasure token. (It's an artifact with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
card.flavor_text: "Shame to let good gold go to the grave."

card.name: Plaguemaw Beast
card.oracle_text: {T}, Sacrifice a creature: Proliferate. (Choose any number of permanents and/or players, then give each another counter of each kind already there.)
card.flavor_text: Phyrexia's spiral of consumption grows ever wider and darker.

card.name: Poison-Tip Archer
card.oracle_text:
Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)
Deathtouch (Any amount of damage this deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)
Whenever another creature dies, each opponent loses 1 life.

card.name: Primal Druid
card.oracle_text: When Primal Druid dies, you may search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle your library.
card.flavor_text: "The power of the woods is only ever borrowed."

card.name: Protean Hulk
card.oracle_text: When Protean Hulk dies, search your library for any number of creature cards with total converted mana cost 6 or less and put them onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.
card.flavor_text: "Meat and eggs. We eat!" —Borborygmos

card.name: Reaper of the Wilds
card.oracle_text:
Whenever another creature dies, scry 1. (Look at the top card of your library. You may put that card on the bottom of your library.)
{B}: Reaper of the Wilds gains deathtouch until end of turn.
{1}{G}: Reaper of the Wilds gains hexproof until end of turn.

card.name: Sakura-Tribe Elder
card.oracle_text: Sacrifice Sakura-Tribe Elder: Search your library for a basic land card, put that card onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle your library.
card.flavor_text: There were no tombstones in orochi territory. Slain warriors were buried with a tree sapling, so they would become a part of the forest after death.

card.name: Soulstinger
card.oracle_text:
When Soulstinger enters the battlefield, put two -1/-1 counters on target creature you control.
When Soulstinger dies, you may put a -1/-1 counter on target creature for each -1/-1 counter on Soulstinger.

card.name: Thallid Soothsayer
card.oracle_text: {2}, Sacrifice a creature: Draw a card.
card.flavor_text: Some of the thallids that escaped into the fens of Urborg began emulating the Cabal's bloodsoaked rituals in their own peculiar way.

card.name: Torgaar, Famine Incarnate
card.oracle_text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, you may sacrifice any number of creatures. This spell costs {2} less to cast for each creature sacrificed this way.
When Torgaar, Famine Incarnate enters the battlefield, up to one target player's life total becomes half their starting life total, rounded down.

card.name: Vhati il-Dal
card.oracle_text: {T}: Until end of turn, target creature has base power 1 or base toughness 1.
card.flavor_text: "Sir, I just thought . . . ," explained Vhati. "Don't think," interrupted Greven. "It doesn't suit you."

card.name: Wickerbough Elder
card.oracle_text:
Wickerbough Elder enters the battlefield with a -1/-1 counter on it.
{G}, Remove a -1/-1 counter from Wickerbough Elder: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.
card.flavor_text: "Living scarecrows make a mockery of the natural order. Dead ones make fine hats."

card.name: Wild Wanderer
card.oracle_text: When Wild Wanderer enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle your library.
card.flavor_text: "We all began in nature, and nature is where we belong."

card.name: Liliana, Death Wielder
card.oracle_text:
+2: Put a -1/-1 counter on up to one target creature.
−3: Destroy target creature with a -1/-1 counter on it.
−10: Return all creature cards from your graveyard to the battlefield.

card.name: Altar's Reap
card.oracle_text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice a creature.
Draw two cards.
card.flavor_text: "Don't worry, your death will be as informative as possible." —Gorghul, augur of skulls

card.name: Assassin's Trophy
card.oracle_text: Destroy target permanent an opponent controls. Its controller may search their library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield, then shuffle their library.
card.flavor_text: A power vacuum for the Azorius. A keepsake for Vraska.

card.name: Avoid Fate
card.oracle_text: Counter target instant or Aura spell that targets a permanent you control.

card.name: Beast Within
card.oracle_text: Destroy target permanent. Its controller creates a 3/3 green Beast creature token.
card.flavor_text: "Monsters dwell in every heart. We only think civilization tames them." ―Euphemia, Nexus watcher

card.name: Costly Plunder
card.oracle_text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice an artifact or creature.
Draw two cards.
card.flavor_text: No lock of iron is a match for Vraska's will of stone.

card.name: Crushing Vines
card.oracle_text:
Choose one —
• Destroy target creature with flying.
• Destroy target artifact.
card.flavor_text: "Your veil's curse won't stop me, deathmage. I have taken down countless night hunters and this dark plane is not big enough for you to hide." —Garruk Wildspeaker, to Liliana Vess

card.name: Deathsprout
card.oracle_text: Destroy target creature. Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle your library.
card.flavor_text:
"They say nothing lasts forever. I say everything lasts forever, just not in the form you may be accustomed to."
—Vraska

card.name: Echoing Courage
card.oracle_text: Target creature and all other creatures with the same name as that creature get +2/+2 until end of turn.
card.flavor_text: A single seed unleashes a flurry of growth.

card.name: Grapple with the Past
card.oracle_text: Put the top three cards of your library into your graveyard, then you may return a creature or land card from your graveyard to your hand.
card.flavor_text: Emrakul does not grant wishes. Desires simply align to her will.

card.name: Nature's Claim
card.oracle_text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment. Its controller gains 4 life.
card.flavor_text:
"The timeless, tireless jaws of nature shall one day devour us all."
—Sildark, artificer of Omu

card.name: Putrefy
card.oracle_text: Destroy target artifact or creature. It can't be regenerated.
card.flavor_text:
"We are all decaying, always in a state of near-death. One moment without breath and we begin to break down."
—Cevraya, Golgari shaman

card.name: Torment of Venom
card.oracle_text: Put three -1/-1 counters on target creature. Its controller loses 3 life unless they sacrifice another nonland permanent or discards a card.
card.flavor_text: The Scorpion God's sting sends venom strong enough to poison blood, bone, and spirit.

card.name: Black Sun's Zenith
card.oracle_text: Put X -1/-1 counters on each creature. Shuffle Black Sun's Zenith into its owner's library.
card.flavor_text: "Under the suns, Mirrodin kneels and begs us for perfection." —Geth, Lord of the Vault

card.name: Blood Divination
card.oracle_text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice a creature.
Draw three cards.
card.flavor_text: Predicting the future is a messy business.

card.name: Broken Bond
card.oracle_text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment. You may put a land card from your hand onto the battlefield.
card.flavor_text: "I can't bear to see another plane broken before I make my own home whole. I'm sorry, but my watch is over."

card.name: Grow from the Ashes
card.oracle_text:
Kicker {2} (You may pay an additional {2} as you cast this spell.)
Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield, then shuffle your library. If this spell was kicked, instead search your library for two basic land cards, put them onto the battlefield, then shuffle your library.

card.name: Incremental Blight
card.oracle_text: Put a -1/-1 counter on target creature, two -1/-1 counters on another target creature, and three -1/-1 counters on a third target creature.
card.flavor_text: Shadowmoor's main crops are rot, slime, and despair.

card.name: Kodama's Reach
card.oracle_text: Search your library for up to two basic land cards, reveal those cards, and put one onto the battlefield tapped and the other into your hand. Then shuffle your library.
card.flavor_text: "The land grows only where the kami will it." —Dosan the Falling Leaf

card.name: Lethal Sting
card.oracle_text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, put a -1/-1 counter on a creature you control.
Destroy target creature.
card.flavor_text: Initiates once believed defeat was the worst fate possible—a sentiment they quickly abandoned.

card.name: Liliana's Influence
card.oracle_text: Put a -1/-1 counter on each creature you don't control. You may search your library and/or graveyard for a card named Liliana, Death Wielder, reveal it, and put it into your hand. If you search your library this way, shuffle it.

card.name: Overrun
card.oracle_text: Creatures you control get +3/+3 and gain trample until end of turn.
card.flavor_text: Nature doesn't walk.

card.name: Skyshroud Claim
card.oracle_text: Search your library for up to two Forest cards, put them onto the battlefield, then shuffle your library.
card.flavor_text: The forest's constant struggle is to keep the spreading flowstone at bay.

card.name: Contagion Engine
card.oracle_text:
When Contagion Engine enters the battlefield, put a -1/-1 counter on each creature target player controls.
{4}, {T}: Proliferate, then proliferate again. (You choose any number of permanents and/or players with counters on them, then give each another counter of a kind already there. Then do it again.)

card.name: Hedron Archive
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}{C}.
{2}, {T}, Sacrifice Hedron Archive: Draw two cards.
card.flavor_text:
"You've begun to understand the hedrons' true purpose," said Ugin. "The Eldrazi can be imprisoned."
"And how did that work out last time?" asked Jace.

card.name: Rogue's Gloves
card.oracle_text:
Whenever equipped creature deals combat damage to a player, you may draw a card.
Equip {2} ({2}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)
card.flavor_text: Thievery requires subtlety, from the beginning of the heist to the end.

card.name: Skullclamp
card.flavor_text: The mind is a beautiful bounty encased in an annoying bone container.

card.name: Throne of the God-Pharaoh
card.oracle_text: At the beginning of your end step, each opponent loses life equal to the number of tapped creatures you control.
card.flavor_text: "When the Second Sun rests between the horns on the horizon, so begins the Hour of Revelation. Then the Hour of Glory, the Hour of Promise, and finally the Hour of Eternity." —The Accounting of Hours

card.name: Whispersilk Cloak
card.oracle_text:
Equipped creature can't be blocked and has shroud. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)
Equip {2}
card.flavor_text: Such cloaks are in high demand both by assassins and by those who fear them.

card.name: Evolving Wilds
card.oracle_text: {T}, Sacrifice Evolving Wilds: Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle your library.
card.flavor_text: Without the interfering hands of civilization, nature will always shape itself to its own needs.

card.name: Foul Orchard
card.oracle_text:
Foul Orchard enters the battlefield tapped.
{T}: Add {B} or {G}.
card.flavor_text: The stench of rotting meat lures flies, goblins, and young raptors.

card.name: Golgari Guildgate
card.oracle_text:
Golgari Guildgate enters the battlefield tapped.
{T}: Add {B} or {G}.
card.flavor_text:
"Shut the gates. In the Underrealm we will outlast the coming doom."
—Vraska

card.name: Jungle Hollow
card.oracle_text:
Jungle Hollow enters the battlefield tapped.
When Jungle Hollow enters the battlefield, you gain 1 life.
{T}: Add {B} or {G}.

card.name: Karn's Bastion
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{4}, {T}: Proliferate. (Choose any number of permanents and/or players, then give each another counter of each kind already there.)
card.flavor_text:
"I can't protect everyone here. But those I can, I will."
—Karn

card.name: Memorial to Folly
card.oracle_text:
Memorial to Folly enters the battlefield tapped.
{T}: Add {B}.
{2}{B}, {T}, Sacrifice Memorial to Folly: Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.

card.name: Reliquary Tower
card.oracle_text:
You have no maximum hand size.
{T}: Add {C}.
card.flavor_text: Once guarded by the Knights of the Reliquary, the tower stands now protected only by its own remoteness, its dusty treasures open to plunder by anyone.

card.name: Terramorphic Expanse
card.oracle_text: {T}, Sacrifice Terramorphic Expanse: Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle your library.

card.name: Beastmaster Ascension
card.oracle_text:
Whenever a creature you control attacks, you may put a quest counter on Beastmaster Ascension.
As long as Beastmaster Ascension has seven or more quest counters on it, creatures you control get +5/+5.

card.name: Blowfly Infestation
card.oracle_text: Whenever a creature dies, if it had a -1/-1 counter on it, put a -1/-1 counter on target creature.
card.flavor_text: When the giant Tollek Worldslayer fell, a corruption erupted from his corpse to carry on his name.

card.name: Cryptolith Rite
card.oracle_text: Creatures you control have "{T}: Add one mana of any color."
card.flavor_text: The chant was incomprehensible, but its power was unmistakable.

card.name: Fertile Ground
card.oracle_text:
Enchant land
Whenever enchanted land is tapped for mana, its controller adds an additional one mana of any color.
card.flavor_text: The true strength of nature is not the raging storm or the charging rhino, but the inexorable vitality of life.

card.name: Nest of Scarabs
card.oracle_text: Whenever you put one or more -1/-1 counters on a creature, create that many 1/1 black Insect creature tokens.
card.flavor_text: "They are small, but they always want more. Learn from them." —Bontu, god of ambition

card.name: Pattern of Rebirth
card.oracle_text:
Enchant creature
When enchanted creature dies, that creature's controller may search their library for a creature card, put that card onto the battlefield, then shuffle their library.

card.name: Sadistic Obsession
card.oracle_text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature has "{B}, {T}: Put a -1/-1 counter on target creature."
card.flavor_text: Not everyone should take joy in their work.

card.name: The Eldest Reborn
card.oracle_text:
(As this Saga enters and after your draw step, add a lore counter. Sacrifice after III.)
I — Each opponent sacrifices a creature or planeswalker.
II — Each opponent discards a card.
III — Put target creature or planeswalker card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control.

decks.title: Test Sideboard
decks.description: Made to test the filter functionality of deck view page

card.name: Meren of Clan Nel Toth
card.oracle_text:
Whenever another creature you control dies, you get an experience counter.
At the beginning of your end step, choose target creature card in your graveyard. If that card's converted mana cost is less than or equal to the number of experience counters you have, return it to the battlefield. Otherwise, put it into your hand.

card.name: Akoum Firebird
card.oracle_text:
Flying, haste
Akoum Firebird attacks each combat if able.
Landfall — Whenever a land enters the battlefield under your control, you may pay {4}{R}{R}. If you do, return Akoum Firebird from your graveyard to the battlefield.

card.name: Hapatra, Vizier of Poisons
card.oracle_text:
Whenever Hapatra, Vizier of Poisons deals combat damage to a player, you may put a -1/-1 counter on target creature.
Whenever you put one or more -1/-1 counters on a creature, create a 1/1 green Snake creature token with deathtouch.
card.flavor_text: Her subtle smile is suffused with venom.

card.name: Alesha, Who Smiles at Death
card.oracle_text:
First strike
Whenever Alesha, Who Smiles at Death attacks, you may pay {W/B}{W/B}. If you do, return target creature card with power 2 or less from your graveyard to the battlefield tapped and attacking.
card.flavor_text: "Greet death with sword in hand."
